00:00:00.790 --> 00:00:05.000
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:12.290 --> 00:00:18.510 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Please welcome the 14th
Librarian of Congress, Carla Hayden.

00:00:18.510 --> 00:00:22.220
[ Applause ]

00:00:22.220 --> 00:00:23.520
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: Thank you.

00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:27.400
Hello and welcome.

00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:30.250
I'm delighted to see all
of you here with us today

00:00:30.250 --> 00:00:33.850
for our new poet laureate's
opening reading.

00:00:33.850 --> 00:00:37.510
You may clap right now.

00:00:37.510 --> 00:00:44.040
[ Applause ]

00:00:44.040 --> 00:00:45.340
As the Librarian of Congress,

00:00:45.340 --> 00:00:50.280
I'm charged with appointing
the poet laureate consultant

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:54.440
in poetry every year, a
position that, by law,

00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:56.770
is described as equivalent to that

00:00:56.770 --> 00:00:59.740
of poet laureate of
the United States.

00:00:59.740 --> 00:01:03.410
What an awesome responsibility.

00:01:03.410 --> 00:01:10.250 position:56%
The Library surveyed over 120 poetry
experts from coast-to-coast: editors

00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:14.090
and critics, publishers,
bookstore owners, and of course,

00:01:14.090 --> 00:01:16.430
our former poet laureates.

00:01:16.430 --> 00:01:20.090
And in the end, the
choice was crystal clear.

00:01:20.090 --> 00:01:24.250
But before I sing the
praises of our new appointee,

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:27.830
I want to introduce
a very special guest.

00:01:27.830 --> 00:01:30.330
This year, for the first time ever,

00:01:30.330 --> 00:01:38.060
our nation has its own national
youth poet laureate [applause].

00:01:43.450 --> 00:01:47.550
Now, this position was almost
a decade in the making.

00:01:47.550 --> 00:01:51.620
In 2008, the literary
organization, Urban Word,

00:01:51.620 --> 00:01:57.450
worked with New York City to launch
their youth poet laureate program.

00:01:57.450 --> 00:02:01.150
And since then, 41 other
cities across the country,

00:02:01.150 --> 00:02:04.630
from Seattle to South
Florida, Boston to Los Angeles,

00:02:04.630 --> 00:02:08.380
Madison to Baton Rouge,
followed suit.

00:02:08.380 --> 00:02:13.050
And this past year, Urban Word
identified its first group

00:02:13.050 --> 00:02:18.450 position:56%
of regional national youth poet
laureate finalists in the Northeast,

00:02:18.450 --> 00:02:21.310 position:56%
Southeast, South, Midwest, and West.

00:02:21.310 --> 00:02:28.970
And in April, they named the first
ever national youth poet laureate.

00:02:28.970 --> 00:02:31.600
Now, Urban Word didn't
do it all alone.

00:02:31.600 --> 00:02:35.320 position:56%
There were plenty of organizations
to thank for this nationwide effort.

00:02:35.320 --> 00:02:38.170
And please join me
in recognizing a few

00:02:38.170 --> 00:02:41.980
of Urban Words' wonderful
local partners.

00:02:41.980 --> 00:02:43.830
Do More Baltimore, the host

00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:47.130
for Baltimore's youth
poet laureate [applause].

00:02:56.620 --> 00:03:02.520
Dialect USA, the host for Prince
George's County's youth poet

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:05.710
laureate [applause].

00:03:05.710 --> 00:03:09.130
And Words, Beats, and Life, the
host for the Washington, DC,

00:03:09.130 --> 00:03:13.270
youth poet laureate [applause].

00:03:13.270 --> 00:03:18.790
And finally, thank you
to Michael Cirelli,

00:03:18.790 --> 00:03:21.290
executive director of Urban Word.

00:03:21.290 --> 00:03:23.700
Michael, could you please stand up?

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:28.580
[applause].

00:03:28.580 --> 00:03:33.770
There he is.

00:03:33.770 --> 00:03:38.020
Your vision and hard work has
paid off tenfold, and the Library

00:03:38.020 --> 00:03:40.200
of Congress is delighted
to do its part

00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:44.180
in promoting the national
youth poet laureate.

00:03:44.180 --> 00:03:50.470
And what an inspiring young woman
you found to take on that role.

00:03:50.470 --> 00:03:55.780
In her 19 years, LA native Amanda
Gorman has done more to speak out,

00:03:55.780 --> 00:04:00.020
organize, and give back than
most of us do in a lifetime.

00:04:00.020 --> 00:04:04.850 position:56%
I had the pleasure of riding the
elevator today with her grandmother.

00:04:04.850 --> 00:04:07.910
Can you please stand up?

00:04:09.510 --> 00:04:20.780
[ Applause ]

00:04:20.780 --> 00:04:23.820
