00:09:46.410 --> 00:09:52.830
There's a place where this poem
dwells, it is here, it is now,

00:09:52.830 --> 00:09:55.750
in the yellow song of dawn's bell

00:09:55.750 --> 00:10:00.430
where we write an American lyric
we are just beginning to tell.

00:10:00.430 --> 00:10:02.510
Thank you.

00:10:02.510 --> 00:10:38.500
[ Applause ]

00:10:44.200 --> 00:10:48.780
&gt;&gt; Carla Hayden: Well, thank you,
Amanda, for your wonderful poem

00:10:48.780 --> 00:10:54.430
