00:14:55.220 --> 00:15:00.420
A Hunger so Honed.

00:15:02.140 --> 00:15:08.410
Driving home late through town,
he woke me for a deer in the road,

00:15:08.410 --> 00:15:12.350
the light smudge of it
fragile in the distance,

00:15:12.350 --> 00:15:17.270
free in a way that made
me ashamed for our flesh.

00:15:17.270 --> 00:15:24.200
His hand on my hand, even the
weight of our voices not speaking.

00:15:24.200 --> 00:15:31.070
I watched a long time, and a long
time after we were too far to see,

00:15:31.070 --> 00:15:38.000
told myself I still saw it nosing
the shrubs, all phantom and shadow,

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:41.980
so silent it must have
seemed I hadn't wakened.

00:15:41.980 --> 00:15:46.150
But passed into a deeper,
more cogent state of dream.

00:15:46.150 --> 00:15:50.020
The mind a dark city,
a disappearing,

00:15:50.020 --> 00:15:54.890 position:56%
